problem.markdown:
You want to test your new implementation of RMSProp. The two following equations are element-wise operations over the parameter vectors and the function f.

\( v_t = \beta v_{t-1} + (1 - \beta)f'(x_t)^2 \) the preconditioning term 
\( x_{t+1} = x_t - \frac{\eta}{\sqrt{v_t} +\epsilon} f'(x_t) \) the update rule

We use the following test function  \(f(a,b) = a^2+2b^2 \) and the following initial conditions: \( x_1=(2, 1), v_0=(0.1, 0.1)\) and parameters \(\beta=0.9\), \(\eta=0.1\) and you can neglect \(\epsilon\) in this exercise. Provide your answer with 3 significant figures (e.g. \( 0.123\))


>>a) What is the value of the test function evaluated at \(x_1=(2,1)=(a,b)\)? <<

(x) 6 {{Correct}}
( ) 10 {{Incorrect}}
( ) 12 {{Incorrect}}
( ) 24 {{Incorrect}}

>>b) What is the value of \(x_2\)?<<
(x) (1.69, 0.69) {{Correct}}
( ) (2.12, 1.24) {{Incorrect}}
( ) (-1.21, 0.69) {{Incorrect}}
( ) (-1.14, 1.21) {{Incorrect}}

>>c) What is the value of the test function evaluated at \(x_2 = (a,b)\)?<<

( ) 4.56 {{Incorrect}}
(x) 3.82 {{Correct}}
( ) 1.21 {{Incorrect}}
( ) 2.33 {{Incorrect}}
